{
  "texts": [
    "Even data that are technically available for public use may be functionally unavailable if documentation is poor.",
    "The data harmonization process can help address this issue when it can produce cogent documentation of how the data was gathered or a third-party evaluation of the quality of the underlying data 101, 102.",
    "What can be lost from data harmonization?",
    "Although this commentary was motivated by the observation that data harmonization can help address the bottleneck of data production, this does not mean that harmonized data is is always the dominant strategy for conducting data analyses.",
    "Especially given trends toward increased quantification and datification of natural and social phenomena 103, losing sight of what the data is actually measuring or how well it is doing so is all too easy 104."
  ]
}